+    it(`unbinds listeners from a key`, () => {
+      const { handler, emit } = getEventEmitter()
+      const uidA = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUidA}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+      const uidB = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUidB}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+      const uid = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUid}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+      const uidD = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUidD}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+
+      handler.off(`oneword`, uidA)
+      handler.off(`oneword`, uidB, uid)
+      handler.off(`oneword`, uidD)
+      emit(`oneword`)
+    })
+
+    it(`unbinds all listeners in the keys set when passed ` +
+       `zero args if allSubscribers is called before emiting`, () => {
+      const { handler, emit } = getEventEmitter()
+      handler.allSubscribers()
+      const uidA = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUidA}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+      const uidB = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUidB}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+      const uid = handler.once(`oneword`, () => {
+        throw new Error(`Listener UID \`${listenerUid}\` not unbounded.`)
+      })
+
+      handler.off()
+      emit(`oneword`)
+    })
+  })
